image_analysis.description: A photograph of a walk-in closet. The closet contains a hanging rod with numerous white garments (possibly robes or linens) on hangers. Above the rod is a shelf holding a white bag labeled 'EUROPEAN WHITE GOOSE'. On the floor, there are several pairs of slippers. To the left, a mirrored door reflects more hanging items, including a patterned robe. The walls are a light yellow/beige with a decorative border near the ceiling.
image_analysis.layout: Interior shot of a closet space, framed by a white door jamb on the right and a mirrored door on the left.

notes: The text 'EUROPEAN WHITE GOOSE' is partially obscured by the folds of the bag. The footer text is a standard Bates stamp used for document identification in legal or investigative contexts.
